ActivityCommentText: Was AB31640; Original sample number inadvertently removed. Head of water is 150m upstream; this is upwelling zone with naturally low DO. Dup E.coli, Tmetal & inorganic collected. Current flow conditions : Baseflow. Sampled Only One riffle. No Winter storms. Same Location sampled as historically. Habitat conditions for bugs : woody debris. 2 genera mayflies, dryopidae beetles, water boatman, belostomatids, midges, blackflies present. No crayfish. lowland leapud frog present & alive. Sonoran mud Turtle seen. Tent caterpillars grazing willows. Spring/seeps in top of reach on both banks. Rosgen stream classification was used from previous study.--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Yes; Normal Flow
LaboratoryName: Eurofins TestAmerica - Phoenix

ActivityCommentText: Was AB31641.  Original sample number inadvertently removed. Baseflow-turbid cloudy. Only 1 riffle in reach, mostly pool complex. Large cottonwoods/willows but no saplings. Crayfish abundant. Cows present & historic grazing blw ag field. Beetles, mayflies, bloodworms, snails present. 3-min kick in one riffle. Salt depsoits on banks. Tent caterpillars eating Cottonwood-willow canopy. Gray hawk seen. Pebble counts in deep polls 2-3' deep; we used flow rod to help determine pebble count. Sulfur smell, fish present.--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Yes; Normal Flow
LaboratoryName: Eurofins TestAmerica - Phoenix

ActivityCommentText: Baseflow. Hiked in from Blue Heaven Rd. Some cobble, mostly sand/gravel, lots of edge cover-watercress. 1 log in channel, lots of bar features and excess fines in substrate. Nearly continuous cover on banks. LB incising and eroding; edw upstream, source of perennial flow. Bugs: Bactidae, other mayfly, hydropsychidae, hellgrammite, lavellalidae dragonfly, damselflies, 2-3 beetle spp, earthworm, midges, tabanidae. 3 cohorts crayfish present, lots in sample.--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Yes; Normal Flow
LaboratoryName: Eurofins TestAmerica - Phoenix

ActivityCommentText: Stayed previous night, sampled early day2. Electrical problem with pontoon where gas read full, but tank level low. Couldn't reach upper lake sites. Winds calm, 10-15 mph but growing stronger. Secchi disk went so deep that no longer readable due to distortion, not turbidity. Max depth at 28.37 m. Target sample depth 7.6 m. Depth to high water -10 ft. Air temp 65 F, sunny.--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Yes; Normal Flow
LaboratoryName: Eurofins TestAmerica - Phoenix

ActivityCommentText: Baseflow conditions, Bug kicks in side riffle-travertine areas, unable to conduct pebble count due to travertine dominance. Bug sample doesnt meet conditions to apply biocriteria. Travertine & algae=poor habitat for macroinverts; side pools have more habitat. Excellent riparian corridor, cover, diversity. Heavy recreation in this reach, but park is closed right now-no other visitors but us 5 researchers. Macroinverts seen: 2 mayfly species (baetidae, Leptohyphidae) leafcase caddis, dragonfly, belostomatids, water moth, hellgrammite. No crayfish seen. Perennial flow. No recent flood event.--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Yes; Normal Flow
LaboratoryName: Eurofins TestAmerica - Phoenix

ActivityCommentText: Beautiful site, Algae (lots) present : Milkweed, Cladophera. No smell, clean of trash. Potentially a early season. No NPS, evidence of large flood event prior to visit. tons of trees in reach. Black flies/ stone flies in the reach all over rocks. Potential for fish but none observed within the reach.  Tons of caddisflies. This site visit was indicative of conditions normally seen in the early spring.--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Yes; Normal Flow
LaboratoryName: Eurofins TestAmerica - Phoenix

ActivityCommentText: Baseflow, clear. On Circle Z property, downstream end. Mostly run, some riffle. Tons of excess fine sediment in substrate and bars. Dozen horses seen on ranch but fenced out of riparian area, but looks like area is trampled/grazed.--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Yes; Normal Flow
LaboratoryName: Eurofins TestAmerica - Phoenix

ActivityCommentText: Chose channel closest to road in Wetlands on the far right. Could be a groundwater upwelling. Very low flow to no flow pool. Just upstream of site, approx. 50 ft. upstream. Tailings are approximately 100 ft. downstream. Ecoli was not required in the SAP we we did not collect - only collected D-metals, T-metals and Inorganics. Could not get accurate flow due to pooling, see flags. The flow was estimated by averaging the two depths with a minimum of 0,01 ft/s velocity. See notes in stream flow measurement section. Syringe method was used for sample collection due to debris and film floating on top of the pool.--- SAMPLE TAKEN: Yes; Pooled, FQ3- Standing water/pools/ponded water only
LaboratoryName: Eurofins TestAmerica - Phoenix
